4 Sec. 241g. (1) It is the intent of the legislature to ensure
5 that all residents of this state are treated equally regardless of
6 their immutable characteristics. Diversity, equity, and inclusion
7 initiatives violate this principle. Therefore, money appropriated
8 to public universities under this article must not be spent to
9 promote diversity, equity, or inclusion. As money is fungible, the
10 source of an expenditure on diversity, equity, or inclusion is
11 irrelevant for the purposes of this section. A sum of money spent
12 on diversity, equity, or inclusion by a public university results
13 in a forfeiture of an equal sum from funds appropriated to that
14 public university, not to exceed the total amount appropriated to
15 that public university under this article. The auditor general is
16 authorized to investigate allegations of violations of this
17 section. Funds forfeited under this section must be redistributed
18 as follows:
19 (a) 10% to the auditor general for the sole purpose of
20 investigating further allegations of similar or identical
21 violations of this section.
22 (b) 25% to the other public universities that receive an
23 appropriation in section 236.
24 (c) 65% to the state school aid fund.
25 (2) The state budget director shall make the determination if
26 a public university violates this section.
